main event: Two round bluish objects, the size of a basketball, rose out of the trees to a 25 degree elevation in the northeast. The objects descended silently in circular flight and were observed visually for 8 to 10 minutes before fading out of sight.
interesting points: The objects were described as being bluish in color and the size of a basketball.
The objects rose silently out of the trees and descended in a circular flight pattern.
Another observer was reported to have had a simultaneous sighting, but no details were provided.
The sighting was initially attributed to a possible balloon, but the descending circular flight pattern could not be fully explained.
The sighting was concluded to possibly be shooting stars or an astronomical event.
witnesses: an observer, with a possible additional witness
